# User-Facing Copy Review

**The maintainer owns all user-facing English copy.** Agents must not invent, polish, or commit wording without explicit approval.

This applies to UI, Discord bot replies, slash-command descriptions, email, error/empty-state text, onboarding, help guides, **and copy rendered into generated images (charts, cards, overlays)** — anything a player or officer reads.

**Goal:** No “inline English” or `TODO: copy pending maintainer` artifacts in shipped code. Copy is agreed with the maintainer **before** implementation; locale files and wired i18n keys land together in the implementation pass. See also [`.cursor/rules/i18n-all-surfaces.mdc`](i18n-all-surfaces.mdc) for locale coverage across web, Discord, and image pipelines.

## Maintainer-preferred flow

### 1. Planning (optional but helpful)

When scoping a feature, include a **copy catalog** in the plan or design discussion:

- Proposed i18n key paths (or Discord command keys / email template ids)
- Draft English for every new or changed string
- Where each string appears (page, component, bot reply, etc.)

Planning may be skipped for tiny copy-only fixes, but the **copy-review step below is not optional** when user-facing text changes.

### 2. Copy review — before any implementation

Present **all** English copy to the prompter/maintainer in chat (or accept their pasted/edited wording). The maintainer approves or edits at this stage.

| Do in this phase | Do **not** in this phase |
| --- | --- |
| List keys + English values; revise until agreed | Edit `messages/en-US.*` or `messages/pt-BR.*` |
| Note maintainer edits verbatim for the implementation pass | Ship TS/TSX with inline user-facing strings |
| Call out Discord `register-commands.mjs` English if slash descriptions change | Run `npm run i18n:translate` or auto-translate |

**Wait** until the maintainer replies with approval, edited wording, or an explicit “use this exact text: …”. Do not start feature implementation while copy is still draft-only.

### 3. Approved → implement code + copy

After English is approved, implement in one pass:

1. **Wire i18n** — `useTranslations` / `getTranslations`, message keys, Discord registrations; **no** hardcoded user-facing English in TS/TSX when the project uses i18n.
2. **Apply English** — `messages/en-US.*` (and any approved inline exceptions) match **exactly** what was approved.
3. **Hand-translate** — `messages/pt-BR.*` and Discord `description_localizations` from that approved English in the **same PR / same implementation turn** (not a follow-up after merge).
4. **Validate** — `npm run i18n:validate` after locale edits.

If the maintainer approves copy mid-session (“approved”, “ship it”, “translate them”), that counts as step 2 complete — proceed to step 3 without re-asking.

## Hard stops (never without maintainer approval)

- **Do not write or edit `messages/en-US.*`** until English was approved in the copy-review phase (step 2).
- **Do not write or edit `messages/pt-BR.*`** except from **already-approved** English during implementation (step 3).
- **Do not run `npm run i18n:translate`**, Google Translate, or any automated translation pipeline.
- **Do not edit English or localized strings in `scripts/discord/register-commands.mjs`** until English is approved.
- **Do not embed new user-facing strings inline in TS/TSX** — not even temporarily. No `TODO: copy pending maintainer` placeholders unless the maintainer explicitly asks to land UI structure first **and** accepts that the PR stays draft until copy is approved and locales are filled.

## What counts as approval

| Counts | Does **not** count |
| --- | --- |
| Maintainer pastes exact strings in chat | Agent-drafted copy the maintainer has not seen |
| “Use that wording” / “approved” / “ship it” / “translate them” on a listed draft | Assumed approval because the task mentions a feature |
| Maintainer edits `en-US.json` themselves — treat their file as source of truth | Prior PR copy, training-data phrasing, or “sounds better” agent rewrites |
| Maintainer says “propagate my English changes to pt-BR” | Implementing English in code before step 2 approval |
| Bulk approval in chat (“I am approving all inline and constant English copy. Go ahead and translate them.”) | Landing English in locale files before that approval |

When the maintainer edits English locally, **read their committed or saved `en-US.json` as canonical** — do not revert or “improve” it; propagate to pt-BR and Discord localizations.

## Agent checklist before any PR with copy

- [ ] Every new/changed English string was approved in chat (or copied from maintainer-edited `en-US.json`) **before** implementation
- [ ] No inline user-facing English or copy TODO placeholders in TS/TSX (unless maintainer explicitly agreed to structure-first draft PR)
- [ ] `en-US` and `pt-BR` (and Discord localizations if applicable) updated in the implementation pass from approved English
- [ ] No automated translation used
- [ ] `npm run i18n:validate` passes

